<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="48" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1285,1775]" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">
The distinctness of 
<emphasis box="[378,403,1285,1310]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">G.</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[468,591,1285,1310]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">Bulbiferae</emphasis>
has been previously disputed (
<bibRefCitation author="Zarrei, M. &amp; Wilkin, P. &amp; Fay, M. F. &amp; Ingrouille, M. J. &amp; Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W." box="[951,1159,1285,1311]" pageId="4" pageNumber="48" pagination="125 - 142" refId="ref11349" refString="Zarrei, M., Wilkin, P., Fay, M. F., Ingrouille, M. J., Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W. (2009) Molecular systematics of Gagea and Lloydia (Liliaceae; Liliales): implications of analyses of nuclear ribosomal and plastid sequences for infrageneric classification. Annals of Botany 104: 125 - 142." type="journal article" year="2009">
Zarrei 
<emphasis box="[1031,1089,1285,1310]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">et al.</emphasis>
2009
</bibRefCitation>
). In analyses conducted by 
<bibRefCitation author="Peterson, A. &amp; Levichev, I. G. &amp; Peterson, J." box="[189,449,1324,1350]" pageId="4" pageNumber="48" pagination="446 - 465" refId="ref10393" refString="Peterson, A., Levichev, I. G. &amp; Peterson, J. (2008) Systematics of Gagea and Lloydia (Liliaceae) and infrageneric classification of Gagea based on molecular and morphological data. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 46: 446 - 465." type="journal article" year="2008">
Peterson 
<emphasis box="[300,361,1324,1349]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">et al.</emphasis>
(2008)
</bibRefCitation>
using nrITS and plastid sequences, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Pall.) Salisbury (1806: 557)" authorityName="Salisbury" authorityPageNumber="557" authorityYear="1806" baseAuthorityName="Pall." box="[886,1386,1324,1350]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="4" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bulbifera">
<emphasis box="[886,1030,1324,1349]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">G. bulbifera</emphasis>
(Pall.) 
<bibRefCitation author="Salisbury, R. A." box="[1121,1386,1324,1350]" pageId="4" pageNumber="48" pagination="553 - 557" refId="ref10724" refString="Salisbury, R. A. (1806) On the characters of a distinct genus hitherto confounded with Ornithogalum, and called Gagea; with some remarks on the importance of the inflorescence in distinguishing genera. Annals of Botany 2: 553 - 557." type="journal article" year="1806">Salisbury (1806: 557)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, the only species from this section included in their study, was in their clade A, corresponding to 
<emphasis box="[1343,1369,1363,1388]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">G.</emphasis>
sect. 
<taxonomicName authority="G.F.Hoffmann, 1814" authorityName="G.F.Hoffmann" authorityYear="1814" box="[151,327,1401,1426]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Platyspermum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,327,1401,1426]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">Platyspermum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(clade C) in 
<bibRefCitation author="Zarrei, M. &amp; Wilkin, P. &amp; Fay, M. F. &amp; Ingrouille, M. J. &amp; Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W." box="[492,734,1401,1427]" pageId="4" pageNumber="48" pagination="125 - 142" refId="ref11349" refString="Zarrei, M., Wilkin, P., Fay, M. F., Ingrouille, M. J., Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W. (2009) Molecular systematics of Gagea and Lloydia (Liliaceae; Liliales): implications of analyses of nuclear ribosomal and plastid sequences for infrageneric classification. Annals of Botany 104: 125 - 142." type="journal article" year="2009">
Zarrei 
<emphasis box="[577,639,1401,1426]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">et al.</emphasis>
(2009)
</bibRefCitation>
. In the last paper, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Salisbury" authorityYear="1806" baseAuthorityName="Pall." box="[964,1110,1401,1426]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="4" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bulbifera">
<emphasis box="[964,1110,1401,1426]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">G. bulbifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is sister to clade C with a bootstrap (BP) of 100% in the analysis using nrITS sequence data (Figure 1, 
<bibRefCitation author="Zarrei, M. &amp; Wilkin, P. &amp; Fay, M. F. &amp; Ingrouille, M. J. &amp; Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W." box="[1071,1283,1440,1466]" pageId="4" pageNumber="48" pagination="125 - 142" refId="ref11349" refString="Zarrei, M., Wilkin, P., Fay, M. F., Ingrouille, M. J., Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W. (2009) Molecular systematics of Gagea and Lloydia (Liliaceae; Liliales): implications of analyses of nuclear ribosomal and plastid sequences for infrageneric classification. Annals of Botany 104: 125 - 142." type="journal article" year="2009">
Zarrei 
<emphasis box="[1151,1211,1440,1465]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">et al.</emphasis>
2009
</bibRefCitation>
); in the trees from plastid data (Figure 4, 
<bibRefCitation author="Zarrei, M. &amp; Wilkin, P. &amp; Fay, M. F. &amp; Ingrouille, M. J. &amp; Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W." box="[487,697,1478,1504]" pageId="4" pageNumber="48" pagination="125 - 142" refId="ref11349" refString="Zarrei, M., Wilkin, P., Fay, M. F., Ingrouille, M. J., Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W. (2009) Molecular systematics of Gagea and Lloydia (Liliaceae; Liliales): implications of analyses of nuclear ribosomal and plastid sequences for infrageneric classification. Annals of Botany 104: 125 - 142." type="journal article" year="2009">
Zarrei 
<emphasis box="[568,628,1479,1504]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">et al.</emphasis>
2009
</bibRefCitation>
) it is in a polytomy with all other clades. This species has the microreticulate pollen 
<typeStatus box="[418,468,1517,1543]" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">type</typeStatus>
along with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Regel" authorityYear="1879" box="[610,802,1517,1542]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="4" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dschungarica">
<emphasis box="[610,802,1517,1542]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">G. dschungarica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Grossheim (1935: 558" authorityName="Grossheim" authorityYear="1935" box="[861,1320,1517,1543]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="4" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caroli-kochii">
<emphasis box="[861,1044,1517,1542]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">G. caroli-kochii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Grossheim, A. A." box="[1053,1320,1517,1543]" pageId="4" pageNumber="48" pagination="1968" refId="ref9176" refString="Grossheim, A. A. (1935) Gagea, in: Komarov, V. L. (ed.) Flora of the USSR vol. 4. Leningrad, P. 558 (English ed. 1968, Israel Program for Scientific Translation Ltd, Jerusalem)." type="book chapter" year="1935">Grossheim (1935: 558</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Zarrei, M. &amp; Zarre, S." pageId="4" pageNumber="48" pagination="96 - 108" refId="ref11268" refString="Zarrei, M. &amp; Zarre, S. (2005) Pollen morphology of the genus Gagea (Liliaceae) in Iran. Flora 200: 96 - 108." type="journal article" year="2005">Zarrei &amp; Zarre 2005</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Salisbury" authorityYear="1806" baseAuthorityName="Pall." box="[306,500,1556,1581]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="4" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bulbifera">
<emphasis box="[306,500,1556,1581]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">Gagea bulbifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was included in pedicel 
<typeStatus box="[795,845,1556,1582]" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">type</typeStatus>
II and basal leaf 
<typeStatus box="[1053,1103,1556,1582]" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">type</typeStatus>
VI by 
<bibRefCitation author="Zarrei, M. &amp; Wilkin, P. &amp; Ingrouille, M. &amp; Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W." box="[1188,1432,1556,1582]" pageId="4" pageNumber="48" pagination="155 - 177" refId="ref11602" refString="Zarrei, M., Wilkin, P., Ingrouille, M. J, Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W. (2010 d) The systematic importance of anatomical data in Gagea (Liliaceae) from Flora Iranica area. Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society 164: 155 - 177." type="journal article" year="2010">
Zarrei 
<emphasis box="[1268,1327,1556,1581]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">et al.</emphasis>
(2010d)
</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Pascher, A." box="[151,328,1594,1620]" pageId="4" pageNumber="48" pagination="353 - 375" refId="ref10067" refString="Pascher, A. (1907) Conspectus Gagearum Asiae. Bulletin de la Societe Imperiale des Naturalistes de Moscou 19: 353 - 375." type="journal article" year="1907">Pascher (1907)</bibRefCitation>
suggested that this species belongs to 
<emphasis box="[786,811,1595,1620]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">G.</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[880,991,1595,1620]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">Stipitatae</emphasis>
, which has a 
<typeStatus box="[1156,1206,1594,1620]" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">type</typeStatus>
II pedicel and 
<typeStatus box="[1385,1435,1594,1620]" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">type</typeStatus>
IV basal leaf. Morphological characters indicate the placement of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Salisbury" authorityYear="1806" baseAuthorityName="Pall." box="[963,1108,1633,1658]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="4" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bulbifera">
<emphasis box="[963,1108,1633,1658]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">G. bulbifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<emphasis box="[1149,1175,1633,1658]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">G.</emphasis>
section 
<taxonomicName box="[1278,1428,1633,1658]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="4" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Plecostigma">
<emphasis box="[1278,1428,1633,1658]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">Plecostigma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, more data are needed to solve the problem of the placement of this section. At present, distinctness of 
<emphasis box="[183,208,1711,1736]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">G.</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[275,399,1711,1736]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">Bulbiferae</emphasis>
is not supported by any of the available data. It fell as sister to 
<emphasis box="[1144,1172,1711,1736]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">G.</emphasis>
sect. 
<taxonomicName authority="G.F.Hoffmann, 1814" authorityName="G.F.Hoffmann" authorityYear="1814" box="[1236,1405,1711,1736]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Platyspermum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1236,1405,1711,1736]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">Platyspermum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in molecular analyses (
<bibRefCitation author="Zarrei, M. &amp; Wilkin, P. &amp; Fay, M. F. &amp; Ingrouille, M. J. &amp; Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W." box="[390,596,1749,1775]" pageId="4" pageNumber="48" pagination="125 - 142" refId="ref11349" refString="Zarrei, M., Wilkin, P., Fay, M. F., Ingrouille, M. J., Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W. (2009) Molecular systematics of Gagea and Lloydia (Liliaceae; Liliales): implications of analyses of nuclear ribosomal and plastid sequences for infrageneric classification. Annals of Botany 104: 125 - 142." type="journal article" year="2009">
Zarrei 
<emphasis box="[470,529,1749,1774]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="48">et al.</emphasis>
2009
</bibRefCitation>
) so we place these species in this section here.
</paragraph>
